result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher Michael Hebble was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 2:42 PM Defendant Christopher Michael Hebble in court.  Attorney Richard Russell McCue Jr in court for Christopher Michael Hebble.  Attorney Cheniqua White in court for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters guilty plea to count 1 and 2.  Defendant enters no contest plea to count 3.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Presentence investigation waived.  Court orders 3 years confinement and 3 years extended supervision on counts 1 and 2 imposed and stayed and places defendant on probations for 3 years.  Court orders 9 months jail with full Huber and Diversion on count 3.  Defendant must call Diversion by September 19, 2022 and report no later than November 13, 2022.  All counts concurrent and concurrent with 21CM771 and 21CM10888.  Costs due in 60 days.  Credit for 1 day.    Defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program and eligible for Substance Abuse Program.  Conditions:  defendant to complete any assessments and comply with any treatment.  Maintain absolute sobriety.  No alcohol.  May not possess or consume any controlled substances unless prescribed by a medical professional.
